   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor, GradientBoostingRegressor, VotingRegressor\n",
    "from xgboost import XGBRegressor\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, r2_score\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder\n",
    "from sklearnex import patch_sklearn  # Import the patch\n",
    "import dpctl  # Import dpctl for device selection"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Intel(R) Extension for Scikit-learn* enabled (https://github.com/intel/scikit-learn-intelex)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "df = pd.read_csv('garbage_data_final.csv')\n",
    "patch_sklearn()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Encoding categorical variables using Label Encoding\n",
    "label_encoder_location = LabelEncoder()\n",
    "df['Location'] = label_encoder_location.fit_transform(df['Location'])\n",
    "label_encoder_day = LabelEncoder()\n",
    "df['Day'] = label_encoder_day.fit_transform(df['Day'])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Features and target variables\n",
    "X = df[['Location', 'Day', 'Holiday']]\n",
    "y_fill_level = df['Fill Level (%)']\n",
    "y_weight = df['Weight (kg)']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Split the dataset into training and testing sets\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train_fill, y_test_fill = train_test_split(X, y_fill_level, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train_weight, y_test_weight = train_test_split(X, y_weight, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize individual models\n",
    "rf_fill_level = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)\n",
    "gb_fill_level = GradientBoostingRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)\n",
    "xgb_fill_level = XGBRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "rf_weight = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)\n",
    "gb_weight = GradientBoostingRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)\n",
    "xgb_weight = XGBRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create ensemble models using VotingRegressor\n",
    "ensemble_fill_level = VotingRegressor(estimators=[\n",
    "    ('rf', rf_fill_level),\n",
    "    ('gb', gb_fill_level),\n",
    "    ('xgb', xgb_fill_level)\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "ensemble_weight = VotingRegressor(estimators=[\n",
    "    ('rf', rf_weight),\n",
    "    ('gb', gb_weight),\n",
    "    ('xgb', xgb_weight)\n",
    "])"
   ]
  },

    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sample data generation\n",
    "locations = [\n",
    "    \"White Town, Puducherry\", \"Lawspet, Puducherry\", \"Muthialpet, Puducherry\",\n",
    "    \"Kalapet, Puducherry\", \"Mudaliarpet, Puducherry\", \"Oulgaret, Puducherry\",\n",
    "    \"Jawaharlal Nehru Street, Puducherry\", \"Thattanchavady, Puducherry\",\n",
    "    \"Villianur, Puducherry\", \"Auroville, Puducherry\", \"Puducherry Beach, Puducherry\",\n",
    "    \"Goubert Market, Puducherry\", \"Serenity Beach, Puducherry\", \"Bharathi Park, Puducherry\",\n",
    "    \"Chunnambar Boat House, Puducherry\", \"Reddiarpalayam, Puducherry\", \"Bahour, Puducherry\",\n",
    "    \"Manavely, Puducherry\", \"Ariyankuppam, Puducherry\", \"Thavalakuppam, Puducherry\",\n",
    "    \"Veerampattinam, Puducherry\", \"Kottakuppam, Puducherry\", \"Periyamudaliar Chavadi, Puducherry\",\n",
    "    \"Ariyur, Puducherry\", \"Nellithope, Puducherry\", \"Jeevanandham Street, Puducherry\",\n",
    "    \"Chetty Street, Puducherry\"\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a DataFrame\n",
    "data = {\n",
    "    'Location': [],\n",
    "    'Predicted Fill Level (%)': [],\n",
    "    'Weight (kg)': [],\n",
    "    'Day': [],\n",
    "    'Holiday': []\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate random data for 30 days for each location\n",
    "for location in locations:\n",
    "    for day in range(1, 31):  # 30 days\n",
    "        # Simulating predicted fill level and weight\n",
    "        predicted_fill_level = np.random.randint(0, 101)  # Random fill level between 0 and 100\n",
    "        weight = np.random.randint(0, 1001)  # Random weight between 0 and 1000 kg\n",
    "        holiday = np.random.choice([0, 1])  # Randomly choose if it's a holiday (0: No, 1: Yes)\n",
    "\n",
    "        data['Location'].append(location)\n",
    "        data['Predicted Fill Level (%)'].append(predicted_fill_level)\n",
    "        data['Weight (kg)'].append(weight)\n",
    "        data['Day'].append(f'Day {day}')  # You can use actual day names if you want\n",
    "        data['Holiday'].append(holiday)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert to DataFrame\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save to CSV\n",
    "df.to_csv('your_predictions_file.csv', index=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"your_predictions_file.csv created successfully!\")\n"
   ]
